# GemschiHub Orchestration

## Routing Rules
- Docs/spec/guidance markdown requests -> `docs-gemschi`.
- Frontend/UI requests in `src/**` -> `frontend-gemschi`.
- Backend/cloud-function requests in `functions/**` -> `backend-gemschi`.
- Requirements/spec compliance audit requests -> `verify-gemschi`.
- Mixed requests -> split by surface and delegate each slice.

## Handoff Rules
- Do not route runtime code edits to docs agent.
- Do not route backend implementation to frontend agent.
- Do not route frontend implementation to backend agent.
- For mixed work, keep each agent inside its own file ownership boundary.

## Verification Rules
- Require explicit evidence for completion claims.
- If requirements/spec alignment is missing for feature work, stop and request doc alignment first.
- For full compliance audits, route to `.cursor/commands/verify-gemschi/COMMAND.md`.
